    <thetext>Description of problem:
Some tests from upstream fail during rpm build or if the alltests.py is invoked. These tests get invoked only on systems where python-pygments is already installed and it&apos;s due to Pygments updated version from 2.1 and onward due to some token changes.

Tests affected:
test_parsers/test_rst/test_interpreted.py
test_parsers/test_rst/test_directives/test_code.py
test_parsers/test_rst/test_directives/test_code_long.py


How reproducible:
Install python-pygments (or BuildRequires it) and build the docutils rpm. Or unpack the sources and execute alltests.py when pygments is already installed.


Actual results:
Tests fail and as a result, the RPM fails to build.

Expected results:
All tests pass.

Additional info:
Upstream issue with a proposed patch: https://sourceforge.net/p/docutils/patches/131/</thetext>
